HEADWORD: Sulphantimonic
<hw>Sulph*an`ti*mon"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Sulph</ets>o- + <ets>antimonic</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, a
hypothetical sulphacid of antimony (called also <xex>thioantimonic
acid</xex>) analogous to sulpharsenic acid.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphantimonious</ent>⟦br⟧
